summary:
**Conclusion**

* The Security Council remains actively seized of the matter.
Here is a summarized version of the Security Council document:

The Monitoring Team shall:
(l) Present additional identifying information to assist the Committee in keeping the List updated and accurate;
(m) Collate, assess, monitor, and report on implementation of measures, including by Afghan government institutions, and make recommendations;
(n) Consult with Member States, UNAMA, and other UN agencies, and engage in regular dialogue;
(o) Cooperate with UNODC and engage in dialogue with Member States and organizations on the nexus between narcotics trafficking and listed individuals;
(p) Provide an update report to the special report of the Monitoring Team;
(q) Consult with Member States' intelligence and security services to facilitate information sharing and strengthen enforcement;
(r) Consult with private sector representatives to learn about asset freeze implementation and develop recommendations;
(s) Cooperate with Al-Qaida Sanctions Committee and other counter-terrorism bodies on kidnapping and hostage-taking for ransom;
(t) Consult with the Government of Afghanistan, Member States, and private sector representatives to raise awareness and assist in implementing measures;
(u) Consult with the Government of Afghanistan, Member States, and international organizations to raise awareness of and learn about travel ban and asset freeze implementation;
(v) Consult with the Government of Afghanistan, Member States, and international organizations on the threat posed by improvised explosive devices;
(w) Work with international and regional organizations to promote awareness and compliance with measures;
(x) Cooperate with INTERPOL to obtain photographs, physical descriptions, and biometric data of listed individuals;
(y) Assist other subsidiary bodies and expert panels with enhancing cooperation with INTERPOL;
(z) Assist the Committee in facilitating capacity-building assistance to Member States;
(aa) Report to the Committee on a regular basis or when requested;
(bb) Study and report on the current nature of the threat of individuals and entities associated with the Taliban;
(cc) Gather information on travel exemptions and report to the Committee; and
(dd) Any other responsibility identified by the Committee.
